OL,3,CNature's calendar has gone rogue:
OL,4,CEarly blooms signal changing UK Springs
OL,6,FYou may have noticed: spring now feels
OL,7,Fearlier. That's because it actually is!
OL,9,FUK temperatures in late winter and
OL,10,Fearly spring are rising, nudging
OL,11,Fplants, insects and wildlife to start
OL,12,Ftheir seasonal routines sooner.
OL,14,FWarmer springs aren't just weather
OL,15,Fheadlines ` they're rewriting nature's
OL,16,Fcalendar.
OL,18,FHow do we know that Spring is getting
OL,19,Fearlier?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
