OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1773133489
OL,3,CNature's calendar has gone rogue:
OL,4,CEarly blooms signal changing UK Springs
OL,6,FThis spring, many UK plants are
OL,7,Fflowering significantly earlier than
OL,8,Fin the past. Snowdrops now often
OL,9,Fappear in late January ` sometimes as
OL,10,Fearly as December ` flowering 10`15
OL,11,Fdays earlier than in the 1950s.
OL,13,FHazel catkins are opening around 10
OL,14,Fdays earlier than they did two decades
OL,15,Fago. Early bloomers like crocuses and
OL,16,Fdaffodils are now flowering in the
OL,17,Fweeks after Christmas, while
OL,18,Fbluebells, normally late March to
OL,19,Fearly May, are also appearing earlier,
OL,20,Fparticularly in the South.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
