PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1773133489
OL,3,CNature's calendar has gone rogue:
OL,4,CEarly blooms signal changing UK Springs
OL,6,FIn 2025, volunteer records showed
OL,7,Fhorse chestnuts, ox-eye daisies, and
OL,8,Fseveral other species flowering up to
OL,9,Fthree weeks earlier than their 2001
OL,10,Faverages, highlighting just how much
OL,11,FUK springs are shifting under warmer
OL,12,Ftemperatures.
OL,14,FWhy does this matter?
OL,16,FNature is a collection of delicately
OL,17,Fbalanced ecosystems. Pollinators like
OL,18,Fbumblebees depend on early nectar;
OL,19,Fbirds and insects time life events
OL,20,Faround food availability.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
